Package: timevarcorr
Title: Time Varying Correlation
Version: 0.0.0.9002
Authors@R:
    c(person("Alexandre", "Courtiol", email = "alexandre.courtiol@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0637-2959")),
      person("FranÃ§ois", "Rousset", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4670-0371")))
Description:
    This package aims at computing the correlation between 2 time-series.
    It performs a non-parametric kernel smoothing (using a common bandwidth) of all underlying components required for the computation of a correlation coefficient (i.e. x, y, x^2, y^2, xy).
    An automatic selection procedure for the bandwidth parameter is implemented.
    Alternative kernels can be used (Epanechnikov, box and normal).
    Both Pearson and Spearman correlation coefficients can be estimated.
